    ],
    "summary": "On 07-AUG-2014 at 1540 hours, a 2nd stage compressor cylinder being lifted by overhead hoist and platform crane fell onto an injured person's legs, pinning him. The nylon sling broke due to deteriorated condition and oily substance, combined with improper rigging procedures and poor body placement of the injured person. The incident resulted in LTA (>3 days) injury requiring evacuation.",
